01:04:12,882 --> 01:04:15,418
And above the here-and-now reality.

685
01:04:19,088 --> 01:04:20,923
However, when we say Shechina,

686
01:04:21,858 --> 01:04:27,530
we address ourselves to God who
has never been distant from us,

687
01:04:28,297 --> 01:04:31,133
who stands next to us, or to me,

688
01:04:31,734 --> 01:04:35,338
who trails behind me and
walks in front of me.

689
01:04:35,338 --> 01:04:38,107
Adoshem tzili al yad yemini.

690
01:04:38,674 --> 01:04:46,182
To God with whom I converse, to
whom I pray and cling in times of

691
01:04:46,182 --> 01:04:52,221
distress, to whom I sing a hymn of
praise when destiny is good to me.

692
01:04:52,221 --> 01:04:56,125
 In whom I confined -- I confide, 

693
01:04:56,125 --> 01:05:03,165
and  in whom I find comfort and solace 
and peace of mind and serenity. 

694
01:05:04,200 --> 01:05:11,007
 In short, Shechinah denotes an open, 
communicative, divine presence 

695
01:05:11,007 --> 01:05:19,348
 in nearness which stands against 
separating creator from creature.

696
01:05:22,618 --> 01:05:27,056
 You know very well that Shechinah 
is from the verb shachein. 

697
01:05:27,056 --> 01:05:28,591
 And what does shachein mean? 

698
01:05:28,591 --> 01:05:33,129
 To abide, to be present, to reside. 

699
01:05:33,496 --> 01:05:36,365
 You know what shachein in Hebrew means? 

700
01:05:36,465 --> 01:05:37,633
A neighbor.

701
01:05:40,069 --> 01:05:41,337
However,

702
01:05:42,672 --> 01:05:48,577
the term Shechinah signifies not only
imminence and proximity in a communicative

703
01:05:49,879 --> 01:05:54,283
sense, but also in a sympathetic sense.

704
01:05:55,084 --> 01:05:57,486
Shechinah is the mother,

705
01:05:59,121 --> 01:06:08,230
matronita, who is kind and understanding
and displays unlimited tolerance and

706
01:06:08,297 --> 01:06:10,833
patience for her imperfect child.

707
01:06:12,268 --> 01:06:17,940
And that imperfect child happens to be
man himself, in all his majesty and glory.

708
01:06:18,975 --> 01:06:25,781
Forgiving his shortcomings, overlooking
his errors, and not minding his

709
01:06:25,781 --> 01:06:28,451
nonsensical insolence and impudence.

710
01:06:29,518 --> 01:06:34,790
Patiently, she waits for her
child to come back, to regret, to

711
01:06:34,790 --> 01:06:38,561
confess, and to amend his ways.

712
01:06:39,395 --> 01:06:41,664
She never deserts her child.

713
01:06:42,465 --> 01:06:44,934
She never deserts a sinner.

714
01:06:45,534 --> 01:06:51,140
Ani Adoshem hashochein
itam b'toch tum'osam.

715
01:06:51,774 --> 01:06:58,080
I am God who resides in the
midst of their defiled existence.

716
01:07:04,253 --> 01:07:05,955
In a word, Shechinah

717
01:07:05,955 --> 01:07:09,925
is not -- Shechinah not
only communicates to man,

718
01:07:11,927 --> 01:07:16,499
but also has compassion for man.

719
01:07:16,866 --> 01:07:23,339
She shares his troubles, his cares,
his tragic experiences and failures

720
01:07:23,572 --> 01:07:27,476
for which -- for which he
himself is responsible.

721
01:07:28,511 --> 01:07:33,616
B'zman she'adam mitz'ta'er, the
Mishnah says in Sanhedrin, Shechinah

722
01:07:33,616 --> 01:07:37,520
mah omeres, what does Shechinah

723
01:07:37,520 --> 01:07:41,057
say, kalani mizero'i, kalani meiroshi.

724
01:07:42,124 --> 01:07:45,594
I have pain in my arm,
I have pain in my head.

725
01:07:48,464 --> 01:07:55,504
The same is true -- applies to the
individuals who want to achieve kingship.

726
01:07:55,771 --> 01:08:00,142
because al pi kabbalah, according to
kabbalah, Shechinah equals malchus

727
01:08:00,142 --> 01:08:02,311
– Shechinah is identical with malchus.

728
01:08:04,213 --> 01:08:06,649
So what is malchus?

729
01:08:06,649 --> 01:08:08,484
What is kingship?

730
01:08:08,484 --> 01:08:11,587
How does one achieve
kingship, how does one

731
01:08:11,587 --> 01:08:13,722
realize the idea of kingship?

732
01:08:15,591 --> 01:08:16,425
By

733
01:08:18,027 --> 01:08:20,362
having an open existence.

734
01:08:21,063 --> 01:08:24,166
An open existence is a royal existence.

735
01:08:24,834 --> 01:08:28,938
The king resides in the
midst of the people.

736
01:08:28,938 --> 01:08:30,973
It's quite interesting

737
01:08:32,675 --> 01:08:39,915
that a king in Israel was always close
to his subjects, accessible to them.

738
01:08:40,783 --> 01:08:44,019
Read the Tanach, leader of

739
01:08:44,019 --> 01:08:46,956
a wood chopper, water drawer,

740
01:08:47,923 --> 01:08:55,664
vagabond, stranger, and old-timer,
senior and babe, thief and merchant,

741
01:08:55,664 --> 01:09:02,838
everybody and everyone could
approach the king to complain for him

742
01:09:03,772 --> 01:09:07,710
and to demand justice and to ask for help.

743
01:09:08,944 --> 01:09:10,479
I'll just quote the pesukim.

