01:09:20,589 --> 01:09:23,926
unto the king and stood before him.

747
01:09:25,060 --> 01:09:26,328
Who admitted them?

748
01:09:28,097 --> 01:09:29,365
What is the answer?

749
01:09:29,365 --> 01:09:31,834
There was no need for anybody
to admit them; they just

750
01:09:31,834 --> 01:09:33,169
opened the door and walked in.

751
01:09:35,304 --> 01:09:41,644
And as the king of Israel was passing
by upon the wall, there cried a woman

752
01:09:41,644 --> 01:09:44,780
unto him saying help, my lord, my king.

753
01:09:46,015 --> 01:09:51,654
Such absurd rules as -- about
which we read in the Megillah last

754
01:09:51,654 --> 01:09:53,689
week, "ki chol ish v'ishah 

755
01:09:56,325 --> 01:09:58,661
asher yavo… el hechatzer hapnimis

756
01:10:00,429 --> 01:10:05,668
asher lo yikarei achas daso l'hamis
levad mei'asher yoshit lo hamelech

757
01:10:05,668 --> 01:10:07,770
es sharvit hazahav v'chayah."

758
01:10:08,504 --> 01:10:12,708
That appearing before the king in
the inner courtyard without the

759
01:10:12,708 --> 01:10:16,679
invitation of the king, there is only
one outcome, that he is put to death.

