01:13:16,458 --> 01:13:20,629
 malchus in Yahadus according to our view 

794
01:13:20,629 --> 01:13:25,467
means integration 
of the individual in the community 

795
01:13:25,467 --> 01:13:30,839
 and existential all-inclusiveness and openness.

796
01:13:32,274 --> 01:13:34,710
 And let me tell you something. 

797
01:13:34,710 --> 01:13:40,883
 It is not just pseudo-philosophy, what I tell you now. 

798
01:13:41,517 --> 01:13:43,185
 It's more than that. 

799
01:13:43,185 --> 01:13:44,553
 It’s of practical relevance. 

800
01:13:44,987 --> 01:13:47,890
 Malchus within Yahadus means 

801
01:13:47,890 --> 01:13:50,793
the acceptance of the Klal Yisrael.  

802
01:13:51,393 --> 01:13:53,228
Good or bad.

803
01:13:54,663 --> 01:13:58,434
 Whether the Klal Yisrael consists 
of sinners or saints. 

804
01:13:59,635 --> 01:14:02,805
 We must accept the Klal Yisrael as it is, 

805
01:14:02,805 --> 01:14:05,541
 and open our existence to the Klal Yisrael. 

806
01:14:05,741 --> 01:14:11,647
 Any acts of dividing the Klal Yisrael, 
any acts of separating people, 

807
01:14:11,647 --> 01:14:14,216
 of creating a sectarian philosophy. 

808
01:14:14,516 --> 01:14:23,358
 Any acts which is out to 
promote and cultivate isolationism 

809
01:14:24,226 --> 01:14:28,030
 and modern religious egocentrism 

810
01:14:28,030 --> 01:14:29,865
 and self-righteousness 

811
01:14:29,865 --> 01:14:34,336
 violates the principle of existential openness.

812
01:14:35,938 --> 01:14:37,873
 Who is a king? 

813
01:14:37,873 --> 01:14:41,076
 A Jew is, who opens himself up. 

814
01:14:41,076 --> 01:14:43,445
 He opens himself up to the Klal Yisrael. 

815
01:14:43,779 --> 01:14:46,515
 And embraces the entire Klal Yisrael, 

816
01:14:46,515 --> 01:14:49,051
 without excluding anybody. 

817
01:14:54,556 --> 01:14:57,626
 The king's existential openness 

818
01:14:57,726 --> 01:15:01,063
 is both of a communicative 

819
01:15:01,063 --> 01:15:03,932
 as well as a sympathetic nature. 

820
01:15:05,701 --> 01:15:11,039
 That's what I call communicative 
existential openness, 

821
01:15:11,707 --> 01:15:18,447
 when I remember that God's concern 
embraces everybody.

822
01:15:22,184 --> 01:15:26,321
 But there is also, I mean, the 
Shechinah as I said before, 

823
01:15:26,321 --> 01:15:30,759
 not only communicates with man, 
but suffers with him, 

824
01:15:30,759 --> 01:15:32,694
 has compassion with him, 

825
01:15:32,694 --> 01:15:35,631
 participates in his struggles. 

826
01:15:39,034 --> 01:15:41,637
 So must the king's existence 

827
01:15:42,004 --> 01:15:44,973
 be an open one not only in a 
communicative sense, 

828
01:15:45,307 --> 01:15:47,543
 but also in a sympathetic sense.

829
01:15:48,977 --> 01:15:50,812
Rambam, speaking of

830
01:15:50,812 --> 01:15:55,250
the king, uses a very strange
term -- not term, phrase.

831
01:15:55,551 --> 01:16:01,857
"Mipnei shelibo lev kol
Yisrael." The heart of the king

832
01:16:02,224 --> 01:16:03,292
 is the heart of the kehila.

833
01:16:05,127 --> 01:16:09,197
Malchus requires of man not only to be

834
01:16:09,197 --> 01:16:17,005
aware of the existence of others,
but to feel -- but also to feel, to

835
01:16:17,005 --> 01:16:20,842
experience their existence, as if it

836
01:16:20,842 --> 01:16:23,512
were his own.

837
01:16:23,946 --> 01:16:32,888
In other words, malchus requires
of man to join and sit together to

838
01:16:32,888 --> 01:16:40,762
share his ambitions, dreams, and
particularly pain and suffering.

839
01:16:41,063 --> 01:16:41,997
As long as I am

840
01:16:41,997 --> 01:16:54,209
just cognizant of the existence of fellow
