843
01:17:02,951 --> 01:17:04,019
Rei'a.

844
01:17:04,019 --> 01:17:10,892
A comrade, an acquaintance, a neighbor,
sometimes a good one, sometimes a bad one.

845
01:17:10,892 --> 01:17:15,263
Because the pasuk also says, ki
yakum ish al rei'eihu l'hargo b’arma.

846
01:17:15,597 --> 01:17:19,534
If one should conspire to
kill his rei'a, his comrade.

847
01:17:21,703 --> 01:17:25,307
He was a rei'a yesterday, yesteryear,
but now he is an enemy of mine.

848
01:17:25,307 --> 01:17:28,543
Of course, I mean, in the
political community, I mean,

849
01:17:28,543 --> 01:17:30,012
these changes take place.

850
01:17:35,317 --> 01:17:37,185
I am just a rei'a, a neighbor.

851
01:17:37,719 --> 01:17:43,091
The very instant, the very instant
-- the very instant I begin to

852
01:17:43,091 --> 01:17:49,731
perceive -- not to know him but to
perceive him, to feel his existence,

853
01:17:49,731 --> 01:17:52,768
experience his joys and frustrations, 

