946
01:25:56,251 --> 01:25:59,654
his grand-teacher, who trained you.

947
01:25:59,654 --> 01:26:04,425
"Thou shall fear the Lord, thy God,"
this precept also includes the norm to

948
01:26:04,425 --> 01:26:09,063
fear and respect scholars and teachers.

949
01:26:09,931 --> 01:26:17,071
God is not ready to share His
authority and power with the king,

950
01:26:17,839 --> 01:26:19,574
with the political community.

951
01:26:20,041 --> 01:26:28,149
However, He is willing to share his
authority, His power, with the spiritual

952
01:26:28,149 --> 01:26:30,351
community and with the teachers.

953
01:26:33,755 --> 01:26:35,123
Why?

954
01:26:36,791 --> 01:26:44,098
His hameluchah v'hamemshalah is
jealous of being guarded for God.

955
01:26:44,199 --> 01:26:46,801
Why did Yahadus surrender to the teacher?

956
01:26:47,635 --> 01:26:50,705
Yahadus refused to surrender to the king,

957
01:26:51,806 --> 01:26:54,242
To the greatest of all kings, but did

958
01:26:54,242 --> 01:26:55,944
surrender to the teacher,

959
01:26:56,377 --> 01:26:58,246
to the rav.

960
01:26:59,581 --> 01:27:06,087
Two reasons lie at the root of the
Judaic glorification and idealization

961
01:27:06,621 --> 01:27:08,256
of the teacher, of the rav.

962
01:27:08,756 --> 01:27:15,797
First, the authority of the
rav is not imposed upon the pupil.

963
01:27:18,866 --> 01:27:22,837
No political instrument is used.

964
01:27:23,371 --> 01:27:27,775
No coercive action is undertaken

965
01:27:29,444 --> 01:27:32,780
to force the authority of
the rav upon the pupil.

966
01:27:33,781 --> 01:27:36,584
The talmid of

967
01:27:36,584 --> 01:27:40,288
his own free will yields to
the authority of the teacher.

968
01:27:40,922 --> 01:27:45,360
He joyfully so -- joyfully submits
to his -- to his way of thinking.

969
01:27:46,027 --> 01:27:51,666
At times, the teacher felt -- feels
embarrassed by the deference of the

970
01:27:51,666 --> 01:27:58,006
pupil and by the bad habit -- 
to imitate the teacher.

971
01:28:01,809 --> 01:28:08,483
At times, while political authority
of the king is nurtured by fear,

972
01:28:09,784 --> 01:28:15,723
spiritual authority of the rav is
rooted in deep affection and respect.

973
01:28:18,026 --> 01:28:19,160
Teacher, yes.

974
01:28:19,160 --> 01:28:27,201
Yes, teacher is a master like the king is
a master, but the mastery of the teacher

975
01:28:30,138 --> 01:28:34,442
does not result in slavery of
the pupil, but in his freedom.

976
01:28:36,044 --> 01:28:42,583
The mastery of the king principates
slavery of the subjects.

977
01:28:48,056 --> 01:28:53,661
Second reason why Yahadus has
glorified the teacher, idealized him.

978
01:28:54,062 --> 01:28:59,200
And God is ready to share His
authority, His power with the teacher.

979
01:28:59,901 --> 01:29:05,139
Authority and ownership
are identical concepts.

980
01:29:05,907 --> 01:29:08,843
Authority is vested in whom?

981
01:29:09,277 --> 01:29:15,783
In the owner who can dispose
or reuse his property in any

982
01:29:15,783 --> 01:29:17,518
arbitrary fashion or manner.

983
01:29:17,985 --> 01:29:22,357
I can break it up, I can destroy it, I
can give it away, I can take it away.

984
01:29:22,790 --> 01:29:26,327
I have full, unlimited
authority over my property.

985
01:29:34,669 --> 01:29:37,939
The head of the political community

986
01:29:40,375 --> 01:29:42,076
I mean, excuse me.

987
01:29:42,443 --> 01:29:47,348
Yahadus has denied authority to the
head of the political community for

988
01:29:47,348 --> 01:29:52,887
a simple reason: because the head,
the king, does not own his subjects.

989
01:29:53,955 --> 01:29:55,957
They don't belong to him.

990
01:29:55,957 --> 01:29:58,993
They are his equals in
the eyes of Yahadus,

991
01:30:00,495 --> 01:30:03,398
whom he has no right to rule.

992
01:30:04,565 --> 01:30:06,868
God's authority is boundless.

993
01:30:06,868 --> 01:30:08,169
You know why?

994
01:30:08,770 --> 01:30:11,539
Because He's the maker of all things.

995
01:30:12,106 --> 01:30:14,809
That's why He rules all things.

996
01:30:16,177 --> 01:30:22,750
He's the king of unlimited authority
because He is the creator of -- of many

997
01:30:22,750 --> 01:30:27,522
things, of the endless and vast universe.

998
01:30:28,423 --> 01:30:29,791
"La'Adoshem"...

999
01:30:29,791 --> 01:30:37,265
However, in a very strange way, has
always looked upon the teacher, if

1000
01:30:37,298 --> 01:30:42,203
not as upon a creator ex nihilo -- a
human being cannot create ex

1001
01:30:42,403 --> 01:30:49,410
nihilo -- then, at least, as upon a
fashioner -- a fashioner, 

1002
01:30:50,578 --> 01:30:52,280
an artisan,

1003
01:30:53,815 --> 01:31:01,656
who takes premortal matter and
impresses upon it a form upon it.

1004
01:31:01,656 --> 01:31:09,297
Shape something amorphous into
something beautiful and fascinating.

1005
01:31:10,431 --> 01:31:13,000
And Yahadus has said

1006
01:31:13,301 --> 01:31:19,540
that the subject does not belong to
the king, but a pupil belongs to the teacher.

1007
01:31:20,708 --> 01:31:26,547
because the latter trained him
and enlightened him,

1008
01:31:26,981 --> 01:31:29,050
sensitized his heart

1009
01:31:30,918 --> 01:31:35,823
and molded his personality and
brought out his noblest and

1010
01:31:35,823 --> 01:31:38,159
the finest and the best in him.

1011
01:31:39,994 --> 01:31:42,029
And I want to add something: 

1012
01:31:42,196 --> 01:31:46,767
The authority of the parent 
according to Yahadus is

1013
01:31:46,767 --> 01:31:49,237
rooted in the authority of the teacher.

1014
01:31:49,570 --> 01:31:53,975
The parent is a teacher and perhaps the
most outstanding teacher of the child,

1015
01:31:54,876 --> 01:31:58,946
and that's why the child is [inaudible]
as partners who share the -- who share

1016
01:31:58,946 --> 01:32:04,719
the child -- and they share the child,
Hakadosh Baruch Hu, aviv, v’imo.

1017
01:32:10,591 --> 01:32:14,729
Yahadus considers talmud Torah or

1018
01:32:14,729 --> 01:32:18,099
limud Torah, teaching the Torah, 

1019
01:32:20,535 --> 01:32:26,040
as creative work and as a reflex of

1020
01:32:26,107 --> 01:32:30,478
the infinite practice of creation
initiated by God 

1021
01:32:31,479 --> 01:32:33,981
at the dawn of history.

1022
01:32:35,716 --> 01:32:38,686
And which has never come to a close.

1023
01:32:39,787 --> 01:32:47,595
God summons man to participate in this
great, wonderous drama of creation.

1024
01:32:49,363 --> 01:32:55,269
The teacher, the rav, answers
the call and joins the Creator.

1025
01:32:55,803 --> 01:32:58,472
Hence, he has a share in the student.

1026
01:32:59,574 --> 01:33:05,413
He owns him because he's responsible
for everything the student stands for.

1027
01:33:07,648 --> 01:33:15,156
And it's self-evident that
with ownership comes authority.

1028
01:33:15,156 --> 01:33:20,695
"V'es ha'nefesh asher asu b'Charan."
I don't have to reach out too far.

1029
01:33:21,662 --> 01:33:22,897
The souls which

1030
01:33:22,897 --> 01:33:24,231
they made in Charan.

1031
01:33:24,231 --> 01:33:25,433
How can you make a soul?

1032
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:26,901
Only God can make a soul.

1033
01:33:27,101 --> 01:33:29,837
How could Abraham and Sarah
make souls -- create souls?

1034
01:33:30,671 --> 01:33:36,310
So Chazal say, "Melamed sh'Avraham
m'gayer es ha'anashim," Abraham

1035
01:33:36,344 --> 01:33:40,548
made these souls because -- because he
enlightened and taught them, "v'Sarah

1036
01:33:40,548 --> 01:33:46,420
es ha'nashim," likewise did Sarah
participate in the creative gesture?

1037
01:33:46,420 --> 01:33:49,357
Because she taught and enlightened people.

1038
01:33:55,663 --> 01:34:02,737
As a matter of fact, the creative,
didactic gesture -- the educational

1039
01:34:02,737 --> 01:34:09,644
gesture of teaching consists in
the opening up of one's existence.

1040
01:34:10,111 --> 01:34:11,946
It's not a mechanical practice.

