01:36:17,872 --> 01:36:22,510
The glorious -- tradition
of Malchus Beis David,

1068
01:36:23,778 --> 01:36:29,784
which is supposed to find its
culmination in the King Messiah.

1069
01:36:30,117 --> 01:36:34,321
Of course, it's a principal
tenant of our credo.

1070
01:36:34,922 --> 01:36:42,763
Rests not upon the king at the
head of a political community but

1071
01:36:42,763 --> 01:36:46,367
upon the king-teacher doctrine.

1072
01:36:47,601 --> 01:36:49,737
Who is the Messiah?

1073
01:36:53,240 --> 01:36:56,844
A politically powerful monarch?

1074
01:36:56,844 --> 01:36:58,145
Certainly not.

1075
01:36:58,145 --> 01:36:59,580
Who is he?

1076
01:37:02,416 --> 01:37:07,621
A -- one whose authority
was established by force?

1077
01:37:08,322 --> 01:37:09,657
Certainly not -- no.

1078
01:37:10,891 --> 01:37:12,359
Who is he?

1079
01:37:13,227 --> 01:37:19,633
The Messiah is a great, wonderous
teacher, prophet, who will

1080
01:37:19,633 --> 01:37:25,840
teach, instruct, enlighten, and
by so doing, redeem the world.

1081
01:37:28,075 --> 01:37:30,377
I don't have to quote the Rambam for that.

