couldn't have said it in more explicit
terms that the idea of malchus is the

1095
01:38:33,908 --> 01:38:38,779
synthesis or the merger of king/teacher.

1096
01:38:38,779 --> 01:38:45,953
And please, those who take philosophy
and take Plato, please don't confuse this

1097
01:38:45,953 --> 01:38:48,522
theory with Plato's theory of the state.

1098
01:38:48,522 --> 01:38:51,992
There is no -- there's

1099
01:38:51,992 --> 01:38:53,661
no common denominator.

1100
01:38:55,362 --> 01:39:01,802
Malchut -- I repeat, Malchut
achieves its complete realization

1101
01:39:02,503 --> 01:39:04,571
in the teacher-king union.

1102
01:39:04,571 --> 01:39:06,840
Not teachers' union but teach-king union.

1103
01:39:12,613 --> 01:39:15,249
Let me just give you one example.

1104
01:39:15,816 --> 01:39:22,256
We have a rule in Talmud, "Moshe Rabbeinu
melech hayah," Moshe Rabbeinu was a king,

1105
01:39:22,890 --> 01:39:24,758
halachically.

1106
01:39:25,392 --> 01:39:26,593
There is a pasuk, basically.

1107
01:39:26,593 --> 01:39:30,864
Of course, the pasuk could be interpreted
in two ways, but a Midrash interpreted

1108
01:39:30,864 --> 01:39:31,832
the pasuk with reference to Moshe.

1109
01:39:31,832 --> 01:39:36,971
"Va'yehi bi'Yeshurun melech b'hisasef
roshei am yachad Shivtei Yisrael." Why

1110
01:39:36,971 --> 01:39:38,939
was Moses a king?

1111
01:39:40,975 --> 01:39:49,116
And if Moses was a king, he was the
greatest of all kings in our history.

1112
01:39:49,116 --> 01:39:51,218
Why was he a king?

1113
01:39:51,585 --> 01:39:56,156
Because he was the greatest
teacher the -- the Jews ever had

1114
01:39:57,191 --> 01:40:00,794
and the greatest teacher is ipso facto

1115
01:40:00,794 --> 01:40:03,397
the greatest king.

1116
01:40:08,168 --> 01:40:15,142
As a matter of fact, when the Gemara
in Brachos -- portrays David as

1117
01:40:15,142 --> 01:40:17,378
a rosh yeshiva.

1118
01:40:17,378 --> 01:40:20,447
David is off rendering halachic decisions.

1119
01:40:20,447 --> 01:40:24,151
David -- David rising at
12 o'clock to study Torah.

1120
01:40:25,019 --> 01:40:29,857
David -- David, I mean,
studying from Mefiboshes.

1121
01:40:30,791 --> 01:40:37,831
It's actually what the Gemara says
in -- what is -- it's taken from

1122
01:40:37,831 --> 01:40:43,971
"Tov li toras picha mei'alfei zahav va'chasef."

1123
01:40:44,038 --> 01:40:49,276
Why did the Gemara, I mean, portray
David as the great talmid chacham,

1124
01:40:49,276 --> 01:40:51,378
the great scholar, the teacher?

1125
01:40:52,613 --> 01:40:56,683
Because without it, he wouldn't
have been the great king.

1126
01:40:57,584 --> 01:41:02,289
If David was a great king, it’s
only because he was a great teacher.

1127
01:41:03,590 --> 01:41:07,961
And his objective was
not politics but scholarship.

1128
01:41:11,598 --> 01:41:17,237
Now let me add something else.

1129
01:41:17,237 --> 01:41:28,515
Yet, no matter how exalted the idea
of malchus is and exalted it is indeed.

1130
01:41:29,917 --> 01:41:33,620
It must -- malchus
-- nevertheless, machlus must be

1131
01:41:33,620 --> 01:41:41,728
dovetailed with another idea, namely
